4680 <p dir="ltr">Getting ready to finish up your kitchen remodel? Dont overlook the finishing detailsyour

4681 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/hardware-cabinets/">cabinet hardware!&nbsp;</a>

4682 </p>

4683 <p dir="ltr">With

4684 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/cabinets-kitchen/">flawless cabinets</a>, immaculate flooring, and state-of-the-art appliances ready for installation, the last thing you want to do is add finishing touches that clash with your design choices or clutter up your polished look.&nbsp;

4685 </p>

4686 <p dir="ltr">In this guide, we will explore the details of kitchen cabinet hardware so you can pick pieces that maximize the overall function of your kitchen and help harmonize your overall kitchen style.</p>

4791 <h3>

4792 <strong>Cabinet Knobs</strong>

4793 </h3>

4794 </div>

4795 </div>

4796 </div>

4797 </div>

4798 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-SINGLE_IMAGE-aafb--e-bc-cbfced">

4813 <div>

4814 <p>

4815 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/hardware-cabinet-knobs/">Knobs</a> are one of the most common kitchen hardware types for opening cabinets and drawers. They are most commonly round or square and only require drilling one hole for installation. This is great if youre not ready to commit to drilling multiple holes in your beautiful cabinets to install a pull.

4816 </p>

4844 <strong>Cabinet Pulls</strong>

4846 </div>

4847 </div>

4848 </div>

4849 </div>

4853 </div>

4854 </div>

4855 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-BUTTON-edcbf-add-df-bb-efddbac">

4856 <div class="Button-module_buttonWrapper__9_k6P primary-button-wrapper merce-button-wrapper">

4858 <div class="merce-button button Button-module_button__UZ69c" style="margin: 0px; width: 100%;">Browse Cabinet Pulls</div>

4859 </a>

4861 </div>

4862 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-bda-dd--af-eee">

4864 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

4865 <div>

4866 <p>If youre looking for hardware that is a little more modern and is extremely easy to grasp,

4867 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/hardware-cabinet-pulls/">pulls</a> may be the best option for you! Pulls offer more leverage for opening heavy kitchen drawers and require less dexterity to use (which is helpful if your family members are older or have a disability).&nbsp;

4868 </p>

4869 <p dir="ltr">Pulls also require more planning since they require drilling two holes before they are attached to your cabinets. Plus, they take up more space.&nbsp;</p>

4870 <p dir="ltr">While pulls come in a wide variety of shapes and styles, the following sections outline the three most common subcategories of pulls.</p>

4910 <p>

4911 <em>

4912 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Finger Pulls</span>

4913 </em>

4914 </p>

4915 </div>

4916 </div>

4917 </div>

4918 </div>

4919 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-bbccf-ac--ac-dea">

4920 <div>

4921 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

4922 <div>

4923 <p dir="ltr">While both knobs and other types of pulls are installed by drilling holes through the cabinet or drawer, finger pulls are mounted to the top or bottom of the drawer with only the front lip exposed as the pull. Finger pulls are sturdy and sleek.</p>

4964 <em>

4965 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Cup Pulls</span>

4975 <div>

4976 <p dir="ltr">Cup pulls are shaped like cups. You use them by sliding your fingers up and underneath the cup to grasp it and pull. Cup pulls are timeless and match a variety of interior design styles.&nbsp;</p>

5028 <div>

5029 <p>Standard pulls are the most common type of pull. They usually allow you to wrap your entire hand around the pull. These pulls can be completely straight or have embellished curves or angles for decoration.</p>

5163 <strong>Traditional</strong>

5164 </h3>

5171 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5172 <div>

5173 <p dir="ltr">Surface-mounted hardware and pieces with more ornate embellishments and finishes are best for traditional kitchen cabinets. Find knobs, pulls, and hinges made with brass, bronze, or copper in polished, satin, antique, or rusticated finishes. Traditional kitchens tend to use knobs more often than they use pulls, but you can still find both throughout this style.</p>

5214 <strong>Modern</strong>

5215 </h3>

5216 </div>

5217 </div>

5218 </div>

5219 </div>

5221 <div>

5222 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5223 <div>

5224 <p dir="ltr">Stick to sleek, minimally detailed pulls and knobs in a modern kitchen. Simple, minimalistic knobs are sometimes used in modern kitchens, but pullsespecially finger pullsare a top choice for both drawers and cabinets. Modern kitchen hardware is most commonly made from stainless steel or nickel, with polished, satin, rubbed, or matte finishes.</p>

5273 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5274 <div>

5275 <p dir="ltr">A key element of the farmhouse kitchen is the cup pullalways used on drawerspaired with square or rounded knobs on cabinets. Farmhouse kitchen hardware will often have more rustic finishes using chrome, bronze, gold, or copper. Other popular finishes are clear glass, nickel, and matte black.</p>

5315 <h3>

5316 <strong>Decorative</strong>

5317 </h3>

5318 </div>

5319 </div>

5320 </div>

5321 </div>

5322 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-eeca-bfd-f-bf-ceaadc">

5323 <div>

5324 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5325 <div>

5326 <p dir="ltr">It has been said that cabinet hardware is like the jewelry of your kitchen, and thats especially true if you choose some decorative styles! These styles of knobs, pulls, and hinges are all about adding a unique flair to your cabinets.</p>

5327 <p dir="ltr">For example, while knobs have traditionally been made of metal and were round, you can find options today that are geometric, hexagon, T-shaped, square, cylinder, and more! Some are even made of glass, acrylic, crystal, natural stone, wood, and even leather. You can find similar, more decorative styles in pulls as well.&nbsp;</p>

5328 <p dir="ltr">T-style hinges tend to lean more decorative. Also, some cabinets use decorative metal backplates in place of embellishments carved directly into the wood.&nbsp;</p>

5356 <strong>Pro-tip:</strong> If youre installing hinges that are visible on the outside of your cabinetslike surface mount, butt, flush, semi-concealed, and t-style hingesits best that the material and finish are matched with your knobs or pulls.

5732 <h3>

5733 <strong>Brass</strong>

5734 </h3>

5735 </div>

5736 </div>

5737 </div>

5738 </div>

5739 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-e--cbb-aba-ff">

5740 <div>

5741 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

5742 <div>

5743 <p dir="ltr">Brass is a cousin material to copper, since its technically a metal alloy made of copper and zinc. Its one of the most popular cabinet hardware materials because its very versatile and can even be made to look like other metals. You will find brass and its variations most often in traditional kitchens.&nbsp;</p>

5744 <p dir="ltr">

5745 <strong>Polished brass</strong> is brighter and has a lacquer coating to prevent aging and tarnishing.

5746 <br>

5747 <strong>Unlacquered brass</strong> has no protective coating and will develop a natural patina with use.

5748 <strong>

5749 <br>Antique brass

5750 </strong> is pre-aged and sealed with a protective coating, so the color stays the same.&nbsp;

5751 </p>

6445 <div>

6446 <p dir="ltr">If youre looking for something a little warmer and richer than chrome, nickel is the best way to go. Similar to chrome, nickel cabinet hardware is made by covering a metal core with a thin nickel veneer. Though it's more expensive than chrome, the price of nickel pays off because it resists corrosion and rust better than chrome. You will find nickel in both traditional and modern kitchens.</p>

6779 <div>

6780 <p dir="ltr">We love including silver hardware in both modern and traditional kitchens. The brightness of silver hardware is an excellent contrast against deep and dark-colored cabinets. Like gold, silver hardware can pair beautifully with other types of metals. One of the only drawbacks is that silver can tarnish over time and develop dark streaks. Antiqued silver hardware is a great option if you want to avoid color changes over time.</p>

7091 <h3 dir="ltr">

7092 <strong>Antiqued</strong>

7093 </h3>

7094 <p dir="ltr">Some hardware looks best with an antiqued finish, which is the process of purposely pre-aging the metal to bring out a natural patina or expose other colors within the metal. Usually, antiqued metals are sealed with a protective coating to prevent further aging. Antiqued brass and copper are the most popular.</p>

7134 <h3 dir="ltr">

7135 <strong>Hammered</strong>

7136 </h3>

7137 <p dir="ltr">Hammered finishes are similar to antiqued finishes because they are meant to pre-age the metal. Typically, hammered finishes are made by striking the metal repeatedly to make small dents and imperfections throughout the surface of the hardware. This is an especially popular hardware finish for copper because it hides imperfections or scratches that can happen over time on this soft metal.</p>

7177 <h3 dir="ltr">

7178 <strong>Brushed</strong>

7179 </h3>

7180 <p dir="ltr">Hardware with a brushed finish is created by brushing the metal with a specialized tool that creates small abrasions on the surface to give the metal a softened appearance. One of the main advantages of brushed metals is that they help to conceal water spots and fingerprints. Brushed nickel and bronze are really popular.</p>

7220 <h3 dir="ltr">

7221 <strong>Satin</strong>

7222 </h3>

7223 <p dir="ltr">Satin finishes are so similar to brushed finishes that sometimes the names are used interchangeably. However, satin is created and applied differently using electrolysis and is finished with lacquer to dull the metals shine and preserve the finish. Satin finishes also help hide water spots and fingerprints but are also resistant to scratches.</p>

7263 <h3 dir="ltr">

7264 <strong>Polished</strong>

7265 </h3>

7266 <p dir="ltr">Polished finishes are typically shiny, bright, and very reflective. One of the most popular materials with a polished finish is brass, but you can also find polished nickel and chrome. Polished finishes add a unique radiance to your cabinets, but fingerprints can show up more easily than other finishes.</p>

7267 </div>

7306 <h3 dir="ltr">

7307 <strong>Matte</strong>

7308 </h3>

7309 <p dir="ltr">Matte finishes are becoming extremely popular in modern and farmhouse kitchens. Matte finishes reflect little to no light and create a sleek and minimalist look. Matte black is the most popular type of this finish.</p>

7310 </div>

7324 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-df-a-b-ac-bacd">

7336 <div>

7337 <h2>Size Guide</h2>

7338 </div>

7339 </div>

7340 </div>

7341 </div>

7342 </span>

7343 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-db-eb-f-f-adbcb">

7344 <div>

7345 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7346 <div>

7347 <p dir="ltr">Now that you know all about cabinet hardware types, materials, and finishes, its time to consider the size of knobs and pulls you should purchase. The following guidelines will help you choose hardware that keeps your kitchen looking balanced.</p>

7348 <p dir="ltr">

7349 <strong>Small Drawers&nbsp;

7350 <br>12 or less

7351 </strong>

7352 </p>

7353 <p dir="ltr">Knobs should be about 1 in diameter.

7354 <br>Pull should be 3 to 4 long.

7355 </p>

7356 <p dir="ltr">

7357 <strong>Medium Drawers

7358 <br>12 to 30 long

7359 </strong>

7360 </p>

7361 <p dir="ltr">Knobs should be 1 to 1.5 in diameter.

7362 <br>Pulls should be 4 to 8 long.

7363 </p>

7364 <p dir="ltr">

7365 <strong>Large Drawers

7366 <br>30 to 48 long

7367 </strong>

7368 </p>

7369 <p dir="ltr">Knobs should be 1 to 1.5 long, and you will usually need two of them.

7370 <br>Pulls should be 3 to 4 long, and you will need two of them.

7371 </p>

7372 </div>

7373 </div>

7374 </div>

7375 </div>

7376 </div>

7377 </div>

7378 </div>

7379 </div>

7380 </div>

7381 </div>

7382 </div>

7383 </div>

7384 </div>

7385 <div>

7386 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-dbdb-ba-bfa-d-ff">

7387 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-dbdb-ba-bfa-d-ff">

7388 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

7389 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

7390 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-12__29AUW Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

7391 <div>

7392 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-cfeaf-e-e-be-ddcfdcb">

7393 <div class="merce-column-container">

7394 <span class="identifier-plugin " id="placement">

7395 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-ec-f-fd-aac-df">

7396 <div>

7397 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7398 <div>

7399 <h2>Where to Put Knobs and Handles on Kitchen Cabinets</h2>

7400 </div>

7401 </div>

7402 </div>

7403 </div>

7404 </span>

7405 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-dcc-e-dd-a-adbad">

7406 <div>

7407 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7408 <div>

7409 <p dir="ltr">Knobs should typically be centered horizontally and vertically on the face of the drawer. On longer drawers that require two knobs, they should be centered in the left and right thirds of the drawer.</p>

7410 <p dir="ltr">Pulls should also be centered in the middle of the drawer. On larger drawers, place your pulls in the left and left and right thirds.&nbsp;</p>

7411 <p dir="ltr">Cup pulls are best when installed on the top third of your cabinets.&nbsp;</p>

7412 <p dir="ltr">Deeper drawers that are meant for pots and pans are best with knobs or pulls that are installed on the top third of the drawer for proper leverage.</p>

7413 </div>

7414 </div>

7415 </div>

7416 </div>

7417 </div>

7418 </div>

7419 </div>

7420 </div>

7421 </div>

7422 </div>

7423 </div>

7424 </div>

7425 </div>

7426 <div>

7427 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-efcbcd-df-e-b-cbbac">

7428 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-efcbcd-df-e-b-cbbac">

7429 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

7430 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

7431 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-12__29AUW Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

7432 <div>

7433 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-bfa-b-a-cf-abb">

7434 <div class="merce-column-container">

7435 <span class="identifier-plugin " id="hardware">

7436 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-abcad-cf-dd--aec">

7437 <div>

7438 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7439 <div>

7440 <h2>Cabinet Hinges, Slides, and More</h2>

7441 </div>

7442 </div>

7443 </div>

7444 </div>

7445 </span>

7446 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-SINGLE_IMAGE-fdda-cb-c-b-bdcb">

7447 <div class="SingleImage-module_singleImage__3fWXf fdda-cb-c-b-bdcb-singleImageAlignment">

7448 <img title="nickel cabinet hardware" class="fdda-cb-c-b-bdcb-image" alt="nickel cabinet hardware" src="https://img.vevano.com/4Y3rJzKeMOKlc5nTzEzCte9gavdUEKvt3uREIpysrUY/rs:fill:0:0/q:80/aHR0cHM6Ly9jZG4udmV2YW5vLmNvbS9CbG9nL3Jlc291cmNlLWNlbnRlci9ob3ctdG8tY2hvb3NlLWNhYmluZXQtaGFyZHdhcmUvbmlja2VsLWNhYmluZXQtaGFyZHdhcmUuanBn">

7449 </div>

7450 </div>

7451 </div>

7452 </div>

7453 </div>

7454 </div>

7455 </div>

7456 </div>

7457 </div>

7458 </div>

7459 </div>

7460 <div>

7461 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-fefbf-a-c-f-affeb">

7462 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-fefbf-a-c-f-affeb">

7463 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

7464 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

7465 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-12__29AUW Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

7466 <div>

7467 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-bc-ec-ab-b-effd">

7468 <div class="merce-column-container">

7469 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-bcdb-ef-f-abf-defd">

7470 <div>

7471 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7472 <div>

7473 <h3>

7474 <strong>Cabinet Hinges</strong>

7475 </h3>

7476 </div>

7477 </div>

7478 </div>

7479 </div>

7480 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-bfb-cd--ac-fadbfaf">

7481 <div>

7482 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7483 <div>

7484 <p dir="ltr">Knobs and pulls are important to the function of your kitchen, but if you dont have any hinges, they dont matter!&nbsp;</p>

7485 <p dir="ltr">Hinges attach the cabinet doors to your cabinet frame and allow them to swing open and closed. You should choose your hinge based on the type of cabinets you haveinset, partial overlay, or full overlay.&nbsp;</p>

7486 <p dir="ltr">Here is some brief information about the ten most common types of hinges available.&nbsp;</p>

7487 <ol>

7488 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7489 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7490 <strong>European hinges</strong> are concealed hinges and they fit inset, partial, and full overlay style doors.

7491 </p>

7492 </li>

7493 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7494 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7495 <strong>Full crank (or inset) hinges</strong> sit flush with the cabinet face or box when closed and are best for overlay doors.&nbsp;

7496 </p>

7497 </li>

7498 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7499 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7500 <strong>Half crank (or partial overlay) hinges</strong> are similar to an inset hinge but sit back from the edge of the door to allow a partial overlay on the cabinet frame.

7501 </p>

7502 </li>

7503 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7504 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7505 <strong>Full overlay hinges</strong> are straight and offset your door, so they can be used on full overlay cabinets.&nbsp;

7506 </p>

7507 </li>

7508 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7509 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7510 <strong>Surface mount hinges</strong> are mounted to both the outside of the door and the outside of the frame so they are completely visible. These are great for showing off some style!

7511 </p>

7512 </li>

7513 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7514 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7515 <strong>Butt hinges</strong> have two mounting plates that are connected by a barrel. Once installed, the barrel is completely visible on the outside.

7516 </p>

7517 </li>

7518 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7519 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7520 <strong>Flush hinges</strong> are similar to butt hinges, but they have a slimmer and sleeker profile.

7521 </p>

7522 </li>

7523 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7524 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7525 <strong>Semi-concealed hinges</strong> are best for overlay or face frame cabinet doors. They hide the primary mechanism of the hinge behind the door with just a small part visible on the edge of the door or frame.

7526 </p>

7527 </li>

7528 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7529 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7530 <strong>Wrap-around hinges</strong> are similar to semi-concealed hinges, but they wrap around the edge of the frame to offer more stability.&nbsp;

7531 </p>

7532 </li>

7533 <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">

7534 <p role="presentation" dir="ltr">

7535 <strong>T-style hinges</strong> have a vertical arm that is attached to the cabinet frame and a horizontal arm that attaches to the outside of the door. These are usually the most decorative types of hinges youll find.

7536 </p>

7537 </li>

7538 </ol>

7539 </div>

7540 </div>

7541 </div>

7542 </div>

7543 </div>

7544 </div>

7545 </div>

7546 </div>

7547 </div>

7548 </div>

7549 </div>

7550 </div>

7551 </div>

7552 <div>

7553 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-cf-e-b-c-da">

7554 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-cf-e-b-c-da">

7555 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

7556 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

7557 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-12__29AUW Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

7558 <div>

7559 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-bccf-ce-aad--efbc">

7560 <div class="merce-column-container">

7561 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-cbdf-dfca-b-bcd-caefe">

7562 <div>

7563 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7564 <div>

7565 <h3>

7566 <strong>Cabinet Slides</strong>

7567 </h3>

7568 </div>

7569 </div>

7570 </div>

7571 </div>

7572 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-cbf-fab--be-bcb">

7573 <div>

7574 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7575 <div>

7576 <p dir="ltr">

7577 <strong>Roller slides</strong> are usually the least expensive option and have a small nylon or plastic wheel that moves inside a stainless steel track.

7578 </p>

7579 <p dir="ltr">

7580 <strong>Ball-bearing slides</strong> move on a set of stainless balls and are smooth and quiet. Typically, ball bearing slides are more expensive than roller slides but offer greater durability and alternative functionalities.

7581 </p>

7582 <p dir="ltr">Before shopping, you will also want to choose how you want to mount your slidesbottom, side, center, under, or groove.</p>

7583 <p dir="ltr">Also, take into consideration how much you want your slides to extend.

7584 <strong>Three-quarter extension slides</strong> are good if you dont need to regularly see the entire contents of your drawer at once.

7585 </p>

7586 <p dir="ltr">

7587 <strong>Full-extension slides</strong> are most popular for kitchens because its easier to search through all of your utensils.&nbsp;

7588 </p>

7589 <p dir="ltr">

7590 <strong>Over-travel slides</strong> extend beyond the length of your drawer, allowing you to see all the contents if your countertop is overextended or your cabinets have a lip.&nbsp;

7591 </p>

7592 </div>

7593 </div>

7594 </div>

7595 </div>

7596 </div>

7597 </div>

7598 </div>

7599 </div>

7600 </div>

7601 </div>

7602 </div>

7603 </div>

7604 </div>

7605 <div>

7606 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-ec--ac-f-ebbeb">

7607 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-ec--ac-f-ebbeb">

7608 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

7609 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

7610 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-12__29AUW Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

7611 <div>

7612 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-febd-ef-b-a-dbbead">

7613 <div class="merce-column-container">

7614 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-e-e-b-f-aacedab">

7615 <div>

7616 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7617 <div>

7618 <h3>A Note About Cabinet Hinges and Slides</h3>

7619 </div>

7620 </div>

7621 </div>

7622 </div>

7623 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-TEXTBLOCK-aee--b-af-dbfcd">

7624 <div>

7625 <div class=" TextBlock-module_textBlockContainer__X2cPA">

7626 <div>

7627 <p dir="ltr">Both hinges and slides can have features that can preserve the longevity of your cabinets and make them easier to open.&nbsp;</p>

7628 <p dir="ltr">

7629 <strong>Soft-close hinges and slides</strong> slowly draw in doors or drawers to keep them from slamming (and reducing wear and tear.)&nbsp;

7630 </p>

7631 <p>

7632 <strong>Self-close hinges and slides</strong> draw your cabinets closed with even less effort than soft-close.&nbsp;

7633 </p>

7634 <p dir="ltr">Finally,

7635 <strong>self-open hinges and slides</strong> open by pushing them in slightly to release the spring inside that pops them open. They close with a click to re-engage the spring.&nbsp;

7636 </p>

7637 <p>&nbsp;</p>

7638 </div>

7639 </div>

7640 </div>

7641 </div>

7642 </div>

7643 </div>

7644 </div>

7645 </div>

7646 </div>

7647 </div>

7648 </div>

7649 </div>

7650 </div>

7651 <div>

7652 <div class="styles-plugin-outer custom-outer-style-ROW-cca-b-ad-a-cad">

7653 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-ROW-cca-b-ad-a-cad">

7654 <div class="Row-module_global__1T17H merce-row-container">

7655 <div class="Layout-module_row__3IzXF merce-row">

7656 <div class="Layout-module_omnimerse-column-sm-12__29AUW Layout-module_marginTopOnSmall__2rO47 merce-column">

7657 <div>

7658 <div class="styles-plugin-inner custom-inner-style-COLUMN-cfb-b-c-bd-faca">

7659 <div class="merce-column-container">

14395"css":"","html":"\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003eKnobs and pulls are important to the function of your kitchen, but if you don\u0026rsquo;

14398\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003eHinges attach the cabinet doors to your cabinet frame and allow them to swing open and closed. You should choose your hinge based on the type of cabinets you have\u0026ndash;

14399inset, partial overlay, or full overlay.\u0026nbsp;

14400\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp dir=\"ltr\"\u003eHere is some brief information about the ten most common types of hinges available.\u0026nbsp;

14401\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEuropean hinges\u003c/strong\u003e are concealed hinges and they fit inset, partial, and full overlay style doors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFull crank (or inset) hinges\u003c/strong\u003e sit flush with the cabinet face or box when closed and are best for overlay doors.\u0026nbsp;

14402\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHalf crank (or partial overlay) hinges\u003c/strong\u003e are similar to an inset hinge but sit back from the edge of the door to allow a partial overlay on the cabinet frame.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFull overlay hinges\u003c/strong\u003e are straight and offset your door, so they can be used on full overlay cabinets.\u0026nbsp;

14403\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSurface mount hinges\u003c/strong\u003e are mounted to both the outside of the door and the outside of the frame so they are completely visible. These are great for showing off some style!\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eButt hinges\u003c/strong\u003e have two mounting plates that are connected by a barrel. Once installed, the barrel is completely visible on the outside.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFlush hinges\u003c/strong\u003e are similar to butt hinges, but they have a slimmer and sleeker profile.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSemi-concealed hinges\u003c/strong\u003e are best for overlay or face frame cabinet doors. They hide the primary mechanism of the hinge behind the door with just a small part visible on the edge of the door or frame.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWrap-around hinges\u003c/strong\u003e are similar to semi-concealed hinges, but they wrap around the edge of the frame to offer more stability.\u0026nbsp;

14404\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"\u003e\n\t\u003cp dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eT-style hinges\u003c/strong\u003e have a vertical arm that is attached to the cabinet frame and a horizontal arm that attaches to the outside of the door. 14405ll find.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n"}
